✨️♇ PLUTO ✨️♇ 

Last, but never least, is Pluto 🖤 

Pluto in astrology rules transformations. Pluto energy embodies the likeness of the Phoenix; slain by the flames, then rising from the ashes to be born anew. People with dominant Pluto placements in their chart can see this as a major theme in their lives. When one door closes, another opens, and this revolving door effect of ups and downs tends to be a prominent experience for plutonian individuals. Pluto loves to dig deep into anything it encounters, and plutonian energy thrives in spaces that utilize occult activities. Those with a personalized Pluto influence can find their lives are characterized by intense changes, both in their environment, and within themselves. 

Since it takes so many years for Pluto to change signs, Pluto is considered a generational planet. The influence is strongest when in a very tight aspect to a personal planet. Yesterday, Pluto transited from Capricorn to Aquarius, and while the influence is slow moving, Pluto changing signs usually shows a significant changes to humanity and our collective consciousness. It's in Aquarius, shits about to get weird ya'll 🤪

🌱 BODY ACNE? hey, twinsies! 
With naturiumskin The Perfector Salicylic Acid Body Wash, your body acne doesn't stand a chance. This uses encapsulated, time-released salicylic acid that exfoliates and smoothes the surface of your skin, great for clearing any blemishes. Combined with glycerin & linoleic-rich oils, your skin is hydrated and replenished for clearer skin. **use with salux cloth**

Up next, topicals Slather Exfoliating Body Serum. Lactic acid and urea to exfoliate, and remove dead skin cells and glycolic acid to even out scarring, whether old or new. Even though it has "serum" in the name it's thick enough that it can be used as your body lotion. 

• Use 2-3x a week, ALWAYS remember to use SPF on your body during the day. 
• For my gym folks, just get the body wash and thank me later. 
• Sometimes I use both on the same night but I don't recommend this if you've never chemically exfoliated your body before, some people may be more sensitive than others. 
• No, those tree hut scrubs don't count 🗣️ 
• I recommend picking one and combine with another product that's hydrating/moisturizing. I'll do a proper post with my fav products and routine soon. 

#CareToTry? target $14 and sephora $30, respectively ✨

As Spring *hopefully* approaches for real now, the Gucci Flora eyeshadow palette really screams in the meadow, flowers blooming, summer is coming, to me. It’s so beautiful, I feel like this palette allows for a lot of different looks - be that a cool-toned nude, warm-toned, grungy, soft, even a bright pop of colour with some of those blues! The shadows are easy to work with imo and pigmented, and the packaging is just stunning. I wish I had been able to get my hands on their other, limited edition eyeshadow palette, but I do feel a little better at least having managed to get this one! 💖
The matching glow & care shine lipstick in “They Met in Argentina” (a warm rosewood shade with pink & coral) is also a beautiful shade that works well with the palette, feels Spring & Summery to me, AND the formula of these is really nice, glowy, and comfortable. 

Gucci really is that luxury brand that always has my heart, the packaging is so gorgeous in my opinion, but more importantly, their formulas actually do impress, too!

The best thing about spring is more sun and the best thing about supergoop sunscreens is that there’s something for everyone 🫶🏼 
They just launched Unseen Sunscreen Body, taking their bestselling Unseen Sunscreen from head to toe!  Like its original Unseen sister, it has a cushy soft, clear gel texture that melts into the skin instantly, but is a bit more hydrating because of fluid elastomers that you can almost feel your skin being hydrated by.  I can honestly say I’ve never tried such a satisfying body sunscreen like this before but I love every second of it. Inside you’ll find SPF 40 and emollients that deliver moisture without any sort of greasy after-feel, plus ingredients that are optimized to nourish and retain moisture on your body, which is great, because of course body skin can be prone to dryness. 
Since it’s a clear gel, there’s zero whitecast and it’s also completely free of fragrance and essential oils too! ✨
